1
00:00:13,291 --> 00:00:16,625
[TWENTY-FACES] Since the day
mankind began to dig graves,

2
00:00:16,708 --> 00:00:22,166
offer flowers, and mourn the
deaths of those around them...

3
00:00:22,250 --> 00:00:27,541
...all 110 billion people who
have ever lived on this planet,

4
00:00:27,625 --> 00:00:30,458
have perished,
one way or another.

5
00:00:32,458 --> 00:00:35,916
[TWENTY-FACES] And the six point
nine billion still living today,

6
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,708
you know, the ones who
bravely tread the ground

7
00:00:38,791 --> 00:00:40,416
in which the dead
peacefully sleep...

8
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:41,750
[GIRL A screams]

9
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:44,666
[TWENTY-FACES] ...will one
day join them, and rot.

10
00:00:45,875 --> 00:00:47,625
[TWENTY-FACES]
And not just humans.

11
00:00:47,708 --> 00:00:53,041
Every form of life is destined
to wind up in death's embrace.

12
00:00:53,125 --> 00:00:54,416
[GIRL A screams]

13
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:56,083
[PUNK A]
Hey! Grab her legs!

14
00:00:56,166 --> 00:00:58,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
Yet most of them do not realize

15
00:00:58,125 --> 00:01:01,541
that death is a gift
bestowed upon the living.

16
00:01:03,125 --> 00:01:04,250
[GIRL A grunts]

17
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:05,250
[PUNK B groans]

18
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:07,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
For death is rest.

19
00:01:07,125 --> 00:01:11,958
A mirror, vividly reflecting
one's life, without prejudice.

20
00:01:14,666 --> 00:01:17,291
[growls]
Damn you!

21
00:01:17,375 --> 00:01:18,250
[KENSUKE chuckles]

22
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:21,500
[PUNK A grunting]

23
00:01:24,541 --> 00:01:25,708
[grunts]

24
00:01:26,791 --> 00:01:28,791
Oh, did that hurt?

25
00:01:28,875 --> 00:01:31,458
Well, that just means
you're still alive.

26
00:01:31,541 --> 00:01:33,083
How 'bout some more?

27
00:01:38,583 --> 00:01:41,125
[YOSHIO gasps]

28
00:01:41,208 --> 00:01:42,791
[YOSHIO grunts]

29
00:01:50,291 --> 00:01:54,333
[grunts]

30
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:56,458
[screams]

31
00:01:56,541 --> 00:01:58,208
[KENSUKE] If anything
else happens to you,

32
00:01:58,291 --> 00:02:01,250
well-- here's hoping
nothing will-- but,

33
00:02:01,333 --> 00:02:03,083
If it does, come see me.

34
00:02:05,791 --> 00:02:08,875
[GIRL A]
The Boy Detectives' Club?

35
00:02:08,958 --> 00:02:10,333
[chuckles]

36
00:02:20,208 --> 00:02:24,500
[YOSHIO inhales]
I want to die.

37
00:02:24,583 --> 00:02:29,541
♪

38
00:03:54,666 --> 00:03:55,708
[CROWD chatters]

39
00:03:55,791 --> 00:04:00,791
[radio plays]

40
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:03,000
[MAN A]
Loud much? Damn.

41
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:05,416
[GIRL B] What the heck?
That's hilarious!

42
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:11,416
[YOUNG GIRL A]
Huh?

43
00:04:14,041 --> 00:04:19,000
[CROWD shouts]

44
00:04:29,125 --> 00:04:33,333
[AKECHI]
Ba... Ba... Ba...

45
00:04:33,416 --> 00:04:35,166
Bazooka!

46
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:36,666
Armalite Carbine.

47
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:39,083
[AKECHI]
E. Enarm MMG.

48
00:04:39,166 --> 00:04:40,458
Glock pistol.

49
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:43,333
"L"? Really?
That's way too easy.

50
00:04:43,416 --> 00:04:47,000
Give me something harder.
You know you want to.

51
00:04:47,083 --> 00:04:48,916
[AKECHI]
Let's see. Lercker!

52
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,583
[INOUE]
Ruby.

53
00:04:49,666 --> 00:04:52,916
[AKECHI gasps]
Y.

54
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,541
It's Detective Nakamura.

55
00:04:54,625 --> 00:04:56,541
[AKECHI]
Mm.

56
00:04:56,625 --> 00:05:00,333
Yes? Akechi Investigation
Firm here.

57
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:02,250
[NAO] Got a job for you,
Master Detective.

58
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,208
[AKECHI]
The robot in Shibuya?

59
00:05:04,291 --> 00:05:06,833
[NAO]
Wow, you get news fast.

60
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:08,916
[AKECHI] Work's the only
thing I do fast, sweetheart.

61
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:09,666
[NAO]
Uh...

62
00:05:09,750 --> 00:05:10,625
[INOUE]
Almost there.

63
00:05:10,708 --> 00:05:13,291
Just 500 meters.

64
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:14,916
Wait! Where are you--

65
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:16,625
[ALL gasp]

66
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:18,208
Don't worry, Detective.

67
00:05:18,291 --> 00:05:20,833
I'll take care of
your robot problem.

68
00:05:20,916 --> 00:05:22,916
There's a 30 percent surcharge.

69
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,166
Of course. If you like,

70
00:05:25,250 --> 00:05:27,875
you can pay with that
tight little body of yours.

71
00:05:27,958 --> 00:05:29,208
[NAO grunts]

72
00:05:31,625 --> 00:05:32,750
[AKECHI]
Hm!

73
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:39,791
[AKECHI grunts]

74
00:05:39,875 --> 00:05:43,166
[INOUE] Hey, please set your
phone to answer on opening.

75
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:44,791
Yeah, yeah.

76
00:05:46,958 --> 00:05:48,750
[AKECHI]
What about the kid?

77
00:05:48,833 --> 00:05:49,958
[INOUE]
Hanasaki?

78
00:05:50,041 --> 00:05:52,291
He's got a different toy
to play with today.

79
00:05:52,375 --> 00:05:54,666
[KENSUKE pants]

80
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:56,625
[NORO] Are you getting what
they call a "runner's high"?

81
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:57,958
Nope, no high for me.

82
00:05:58,041 --> 00:06:00,750
[NORO] Still, you're a hardcore
adrenaline junkie.

83
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:03,125
Both excesses and
deficiencies of adrenaline

84
00:06:03,208 --> 00:06:04,458
can shorten your lifespan.

85
00:06:04,541 --> 00:06:06,750
Oh, give it a rest, Noro.

86
00:06:06,833 --> 00:06:08,583
[NORO exhales]
Whatever.

87
00:06:08,666 --> 00:06:11,208
If you don't find it today,
you can kiss your fee goodbye.

88
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:14,541
[KENSUKE] I'm lookin', okay?
Gimme a break.

89
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:16,208
[NORO]
Okay, take the next right.

90
00:06:16,291 --> 00:06:17,666
[KENSUKE]
Got it!

91
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:19,500
[NORO]
Not that way! I said right!

92
00:06:19,583 --> 00:06:21,833
Like the hand you
hold chopsticks with!

93
00:06:21,916 --> 00:06:24,083
Or the side that
conservatives are on!

94
00:06:24,166 --> 00:06:26,541
--Not the Ise Expressway!
--[phone rings]

95
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,625
[AKECHI]
Noro, you're up!

96
00:06:29,708 --> 00:06:32,416
[NORO giggles]
Yes, sir!

97
00:06:41,041 --> 00:06:43,500
Two-oh-two-oh-oh-seven-two-four.

98
00:06:43,583 --> 00:06:46,750
Getting in on the
Olympic fever? Nice.

99
00:06:48,125 --> 00:06:50,041
[NORO] I won't hack
the inside, though.

100
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:53,041
I get the feeling I don't want
to make enemies of these people.

101
00:06:53,125 --> 00:06:56,166
Don't worry 'bout it,
I can take things from here.

102
00:06:56,250 --> 00:06:58,125
[OPERATOR A] We're checking
the log-in records, but there's

103
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:00,208
no sign of who
last used it.

104
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:01,750
[OPERATOR C] The excavator
just reached the utility duct.

105
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:02,916
[OPERATOR D]
It hit the cable!

106
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,250
[OPERATOR E]
It's trying to invade--

107
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:05,541
[MALE OPERATOR 1B]
I know that! Put up a firewall!

108
00:07:05,625 --> 00:07:07,583
But, sir, if we isolate
the main system,

109
00:07:07,666 --> 00:07:09,208
we'll lose all control
of the security network--

110
00:07:09,291 --> 00:07:10,666
[OPERATOR B]
Just do it!

111
00:07:10,750 --> 00:07:12,250
Right.

112
00:07:12,333 --> 00:07:13,500
What the hell?

113
00:07:13,583 --> 00:07:16,250
Pretty fancy trap
you've set up.

114
00:07:16,333 --> 00:07:17,875
Using the robot as a decoy

115
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:20,500
while you personally
breach the system.

116
00:07:20,583 --> 00:07:23,291
What exactly are you trying
to put in the main computer?

117
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:25,250
[chuckles]

118
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:28,666
Rather talkative today,
aren't we, Akechi? It's cute.

119
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:31,166
And you did a poor job of
following through today,

120
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:32,916
Fiend with Twenty Faces.

121
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,541
[OPERATOR B]
Did he say Twenty-Faces?

122
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:36,750
[OPERATOR C screams]

123
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:39,708
[AKECHI] So, when'd you
bust out of prison?

124
00:07:39,791 --> 00:07:43,208
[TWENTY-FACES] Was I sent
to prison? I don't recall that.

125
00:07:43,291 --> 00:07:43,833
[screams]

126
00:07:43,916 --> 00:07:45,708
[gasps]

127
00:07:45,791 --> 00:07:47,125
[chuckles]

128
00:07:47,208 --> 00:07:48,666
[AKECHI grunts]

129
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:57,333
[AKECHI sighs] Looks like we're
playing hide and seek, now.

130
00:07:57,416 --> 00:07:58,750
[KENSUKE grunts]

131
00:07:58,833 --> 00:08:00,875
[NORO] Jeez, there's no point
in being your navigator.

132
00:08:00,958 --> 00:08:03,666
[KENSUKE] Would you relax?
I found this, now didn't I?

133
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,500
[KENSUKE] That means
Melodina must be hiding

134
00:08:06,583 --> 00:08:08,291
somewhere around here, right?

135
00:08:08,375 --> 00:08:10,041
There's no way
it'll be that easy.

136
00:08:10,125 --> 00:08:12,000
[KENSUKE]
Found her!

137
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:12,625
What?!

138
00:08:12,708 --> 00:08:13,583
[MELODINA pants]

139
00:08:13,666 --> 00:08:15,125
[KENSUKE]
Melodina.

140
00:08:15,208 --> 00:08:16,750
Time to go home!

141
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:17,625
Come back!

142
00:08:17,708 --> 00:08:19,500
Stupid dog!

143
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:22,125
[KENSUKE]
Hm?

144
00:08:22,208 --> 00:08:24,333
[AKECHI]
I know, Inoue. I blew it.

145
00:08:24,416 --> 00:08:26,708
[INOUE] If you didn't know that,
we'd have a big problem.

146
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:27,958
Well?

147
00:08:30,416 --> 00:08:32,416
Any idea where he went?

148
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:35,625
Wait. I'm recalling the
facilities' structure.

149
00:08:35,708 --> 00:08:38,333
There are three escape routes
out of the control room.

150
00:08:38,416 --> 00:08:40,166
The shortest would be
out of the south exit

151
00:08:40,250 --> 00:08:41,666
and into the waterway,

152
00:08:41,750 --> 00:08:44,833
but I can't imagine this guy
using such an obvious path.

153
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:48,625
It's also very likely that he
was expecting you to show up.

154
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:52,166
That said, There's only
one place he'd go.

155
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,666
[FEMALE NEWSCASTER]
The robot that suddenly appeared

156
00:08:55,750 --> 00:08:57,708
in Shibuya is said to be
the next generation of

157
00:08:57,791 --> 00:09:01,250
security bots, under development
by Hinomoto Heavy Industries.

158
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,458
No further informa--

159
00:09:02,541 --> 00:09:04,291
You certainly took
your time, Akechi.

160
00:09:04,375 --> 00:09:05,625
[AKECHI]
Yeah, well,

161
00:09:05,708 --> 00:09:08,333
punctuality and I have
never really gotten along.

162
00:09:08,416 --> 00:09:10,291
[MAN C] You still carry that
dangerous thing around

163
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:13,541
in public, "Master Detective"?

164
00:09:13,625 --> 00:09:17,875
[chuckles]
What an evil man you are.

165
00:09:17,958 --> 00:09:19,458
[WAITER A]
Sorry for the wait.

166
00:09:21,125 --> 00:09:24,166
Assam Tea. Your favorite, yes?

167
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:26,708
[MELODINA pants, barks]

168
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:30,208
[KENSUKE grunt, groans]
Gimme a break!

169
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:33,458
[NORO] Just grab her!
It's almost time for my Pilates.

170
00:09:33,541 --> 00:09:36,166
You can do that stuff anytime,
Little Miss Shut-In.

171
00:09:36,250 --> 00:09:38,708
[NORO gasps] Hey, you're not
allowed to say that!

172
00:09:38,791 --> 00:09:40,375
That's moral harassment, buddy!

173
00:09:40,458 --> 00:09:42,708
[NORO gasps]

174
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:44,583
[NORO screams]

175
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:45,708
[MELODINA barks]

176
00:09:45,791 --> 00:09:48,208
[KENSUKE]
Come here, you stupid mutt!

177
00:09:48,291 --> 00:09:49,083
Uh!

178
00:09:49,166 --> 00:09:51,208
[barks]

179
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:52,333
Huh?

180
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:56,833
[barking continues]

181
00:09:56,916 --> 00:09:57,708
[YOSHIO whimpers]

182
00:09:57,791 --> 00:10:00,250
Uh, hello there. What's up?

183
00:10:00,333 --> 00:10:01,625
[YOSHIO]
Leave!

184
00:10:01,708 --> 00:10:05,666
[whimpers]

185
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:08,583
It's all right. I'm just
here to catch the dog.

186
00:10:08,666 --> 00:10:09,958
Then I'll be out of your hair.

187
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:10,750
[MELODINA barks]

188
00:10:10,833 --> 00:10:13,083
Hey! Idiot!

189
00:10:13,166 --> 00:10:15,541
[YOSHIO whimpers]

190
00:10:15,625 --> 00:10:17,666
Stay back!

191
00:10:17,750 --> 00:10:18,833
[MELODINA yelps]

192
00:10:28,291 --> 00:10:32,291
[whimpers]

193
00:10:32,375 --> 00:10:37,666
[YOSHIO] Dammit, why?
I told you... to stay away.

194
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:39,666
I told you!

195
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:44,291
[YOSHIO whimpers]
I...

196
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:48,708
I did nothing wrong!

197
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:53,041
[gasps]
Hey, wait!

198
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,458
[KENSUKE gasps]

199
00:10:55,708 --> 00:10:56,958
[KENSUKE]
Huh?

200
00:10:59,375 --> 00:11:01,000
[KENSUKE]
Hm! You're kidding!

201
00:11:01,083 --> 00:11:04,458
[explosions]

202
00:11:04,541 --> 00:11:05,875
[FEMALE NEWSCASTER]
We're not sure why,

203
00:11:05,958 --> 00:11:08,958
but now the robot is launching
a barrage of fireworks.

204
00:11:09,041 --> 00:11:11,458
Pretty fancy show you're
putting on out there.

205
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:13,791
What would you like
for the finale?

206
00:11:13,875 --> 00:11:16,583
I have explosives,
or poison gas if you prefer.

207
00:11:16,666 --> 00:11:18,291
You trying to threaten me?

208
00:11:18,375 --> 00:11:21,333
[MAN C] Or, we could call
it a draw for today.

209
00:11:21,416 --> 00:11:24,333
[gasps]

210
00:11:24,416 --> 00:11:26,208
Your tea is ready.

211
00:11:35,166 --> 00:11:39,875
[YOSHIO groans]

212
00:11:39,958 --> 00:11:44,916
--[gunshot]
--[YOSHIO gags, coughs]

213
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:51,375
[YOSHIO grunts]

214
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:53,958
[YOSHIO]
Just let me die!

215
00:11:54,041 --> 00:11:55,750
[NORO]
What? That doesn't make sense!

216
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:59,125
[INOUE sighs] Look. If you don't
get it now, you're not going to.

217
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:02,125
[NORO] But to retract their
request like that, it's just--

218
00:12:02,208 --> 00:12:04,791
Drop it. Just tell Hanasaki
he doesn't have to look

219
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:05,875
for the dog anymore.

220
00:12:05,958 --> 00:12:07,375
[NORO]
But...

221
00:12:07,458 --> 00:12:09,625
[INOUE] You're the one who
said you'd look after him, Noro.

222
00:12:09,708 --> 00:12:10,625
Am I right?

223
00:12:10,708 --> 00:12:12,208
[NORO gasps]

224
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:14,666
[NORO] I don't have to take
this kind of crap from you!

225
00:12:14,750 --> 00:12:15,750
That's bullying...!

226
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:17,666
[AKECHI] Would you keep
it down, please?

227
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:21,291
I swear. Sometimes it feels like
I'm running a daycare center.

228
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:22,791
Huh?

229
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:23,958
[PIPPO hoots]

230
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:25,625
[NAO grunts]
All that work,

231
00:12:25,708 --> 00:12:27,541
and it didn't even
have explosives in it.

232
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:28,916
There didn't need to be.

233
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:31,500
Twenty-Faces knew we'd
have to focus on the robot.

234
00:12:31,583 --> 00:12:34,125
[NAO gasps]
It isn't fair.

235
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:36,000
We should have
jurisdiction here.

236
00:12:36,083 --> 00:12:38,041
Security bots are
top-secret tech.

237
00:12:38,125 --> 00:12:39,375
You know that.

238
00:12:39,458 --> 00:12:43,041
"We'll be sure to look
into it." Yeah, right.

239
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:52,541
[DOG barks]

240
00:12:52,625 --> 00:12:53,666
[KENSUKE gasps]

241
00:12:53,750 --> 00:12:56,208
[YOUNG BOY]
Aww! So cute!

242
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:12,958
[KENSUKE] You're sadder than
anyone about it, aren't you?

243
00:13:13,041 --> 00:13:14,291
[YOSHIO gasps]

244
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:21,875
[YOSHIO grunts]

245
00:13:21,958 --> 00:13:23,791
[KENSUKE gasps]
Wait!

246
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:28,416
[exhales]

247
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:30,916
[KENSUKE]
That won't work this time!

248
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:34,208
[gasps]

249
00:13:39,375 --> 00:13:40,708
[KENSUKE grunts]

250
00:13:46,916 --> 00:13:47,875
Stay back!

251
00:13:47,958 --> 00:13:49,125
[KENSUKE chuckles]

252
00:13:50,416 --> 00:13:53,250
Whoa!

253
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:54,583
[gasps]

254
00:13:56,208 --> 00:14:00,916
[KENSUKE grunts, groans]

255
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,458
[KENSUKE]
Jeez, that hurts.

256
00:14:02,541 --> 00:14:03,166
[YOSHIO grunts]

257
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:05,833
[gasps]

258
00:14:05,916 --> 00:14:07,333
Just leave me alone!

259
00:14:07,416 --> 00:14:08,833
[YOSHIO grunts]

260
00:14:12,083 --> 00:14:14,916
[KENSUKE laughs]
Nice one!

261
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,416
[YOSHIO] Stop it, stop it,
stop it, stop it, stop it!

262
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:23,500
[YOSHIO pants]

263
00:14:31,750 --> 00:14:33,041
[YOSHIO gasps]

264
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:36,916
Huh?

265
00:14:41,375 --> 00:14:42,541
[gasps]

266
00:14:44,041 --> 00:14:45,625
[gasps]

267
00:14:51,750 --> 00:14:53,708
[YOSHIO exhales]

268
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:56,333
[KENSUKE] You love diving
into stuff, don't you?

269
00:14:56,416 --> 00:14:58,583
[YOSHIO]
Please stop.

270
00:14:58,666 --> 00:15:01,500
If you get any closer,
you'll die.

271
00:15:01,583 --> 00:15:03,541
[KENSUKE grunts]
Hold that thought.

272
00:15:03,625 --> 00:15:04,791
[YOSHIO gasps]

273
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:07,041
[KENSUKE]
Do you want cider or tea?

274
00:15:07,125 --> 00:15:08,333
[YOSHIO gasps]

275
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:11,625
Cool. Tea it is.

276
00:15:22,083 --> 00:15:24,583
[KENSUKE yelps]

277
00:15:25,708 --> 00:15:30,666
[KENSUKE grunts, chuckles]

278
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:35,083
So cool. You crack me up.

279
00:15:35,166 --> 00:15:36,708
Huh?

280
00:15:37,916 --> 00:15:40,875
[KENSUKE]
Go on. Take a big gulp.

281
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:48,666
[bottle hisses]

282
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:53,583
[coughs]

283
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:56,833
[grunts]

284
00:15:56,916 --> 00:15:58,250
[gasps]

285
00:15:58,333 --> 00:15:59,375
Like it?

286
00:15:59,458 --> 00:16:01,958
Never had it before. It's good.

287
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:04,500
So, uh. What's with
the crazy force field?

288
00:16:04,583 --> 00:16:07,541
If I knew the answer
to that, I'd stop it.

289
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:11,500
I see. It's something you
have no control over, then.

290
00:16:11,583 --> 00:16:13,416
But you can't die.
That's awesome!

291
00:16:13,500 --> 00:16:14,541
It's not awesome!

292
00:16:14,625 --> 00:16:16,333
[KENSUKE gasps]

293
00:16:16,416 --> 00:16:22,458
[YOSHIO] You don't get it.
Death is the only thing I want.

294
00:16:31,375 --> 00:16:34,291
[gasps]
Sorry! Gotta go!

295
00:16:34,375 --> 00:16:36,458
I'll see you next time!

296
00:16:37,666 --> 00:16:39,458
What's his deal?

297
00:16:39,541 --> 00:16:40,708
[gasps]

298
00:16:48,208 --> 00:16:50,208
[KENSUKE] We aren't in
the clear yet, Noro!

299
00:16:50,291 --> 00:16:53,000
[NORO] Slow down!
You're not making any sense!

300
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:55,916
[KENSUKE] The robot case that
popped up earlier today.

301
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:59,041
Twenty-Faces is planning
something major, I'm sure of it!

302
00:16:59,125 --> 00:17:02,333
A fire at Hinomoto Heavy
Industries at a time like this?

303
00:17:02,416 --> 00:17:04,208
[NORO]
Planning what, exactly?

304
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:06,583
[INOUE]
We're on our way. Wait for us.

305
00:17:06,666 --> 00:17:09,083
[KENSUKE chuckles]
Not my style!

306
00:17:09,666 --> 00:17:10,791
--[INOUE] Idiot!
--[AKECHI] That boy.

307
00:17:10,875 --> 00:17:13,250
[NORO]
He's totally holding a grudge.

308
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:16,250
Remind me. What did you
do to deserve payment?

309
00:17:16,333 --> 00:17:18,166
[AKECHI chuckles]

310
00:17:18,250 --> 00:17:21,541
[OPERATORS shouting]

311
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:23,625
[NORO]
He's definitely a junkie.

312
00:17:23,708 --> 00:17:25,625
[INOUE] Keep the trace
on Hanasaki. Don't lose him!

313
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:28,708
[NORO] Dumb thrill seeker.
He's gonna die young!

314
00:17:34,416 --> 00:17:37,958
Why am I doing this for him?

315
00:17:42,666 --> 00:17:45,333
[KENSUKE] Hang on.
We're almost there.

316
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:51,958
[KENSUKE gasps]

317
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,583
[NORO]
Oh, no. It just stopped.

318
00:17:56,666 --> 00:17:57,916
[INOUE]
I can see that.

319
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:01,291
[NORO]
Not you. Hanasaki's tracer.

320
00:18:06,916 --> 00:18:07,916
He's not here.

321
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:09,333
[OPERATOR E]
Hey!

322
00:18:09,416 --> 00:18:10,916
Help me!

323
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:11,833
[gasps]

324
00:18:11,916 --> 00:18:16,416
We don't have much time! Hurry!

325
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:19,541
Hey! Are you deaf? Help me!

326
00:18:19,625 --> 00:18:20,958
[YOSHIO]
Sorry, I can't.

327
00:18:21,041 --> 00:18:22,916
[OPERATOR E gasps]

328
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,791
Screw you, freakin' brat! Die!

329
00:18:29,250 --> 00:18:30,541
[gasps]

330
00:18:32,750 --> 00:18:37,041
[OPERATOR E pants]

331
00:18:37,125 --> 00:18:41,583
[KENSUKE grunts]

332
00:18:41,666 --> 00:18:44,750
You came here to
rescue me, didn't you?

333
00:18:44,833 --> 00:18:48,333
You know I can't do that.
You've seen it.

334
00:18:48,416 --> 00:18:52,166
Still. You tried,
and that's what matters.

335
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:54,791
We're gonna push on
the count of three.

336
00:18:54,875 --> 00:18:57,333
One... Two...

337
00:18:57,416 --> 00:18:58,458
Three!

338
00:18:58,541 --> 00:19:01,375
[KENSUKE, OPERATOR E grunting]

339
00:19:01,458 --> 00:19:03,666
[KENSUKE]
Was worried for a sec.

340
00:19:08,375 --> 00:19:11,375
[OPERATOR E yelps]

341
00:19:11,458 --> 00:19:14,458
[OPERATOR E] Stay away
from me, freak! I mean it!

342
00:19:14,541 --> 00:19:17,791
You damn brat!
Monster! Drop dead!

343
00:19:17,875 --> 00:19:19,916
Lay down and burn like
the demon you are!

344
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:23,791
That's all that I've
been trying to do!

345
00:19:23,875 --> 00:19:28,083
[scoffs] Then do it!
Think I care? I don't! At all!

346
00:19:28,166 --> 00:19:30,208
Die, die, die, die, die!

347
00:19:30,291 --> 00:19:31,208
[grunts]

348
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:34,375
[OPERATOR E gasps]

349
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:37,708
[KENSUKE] Keep acting up,
and I'll leave you here.

350
00:19:37,791 --> 00:19:39,208
[gasps]

351
00:19:40,666 --> 00:19:44,625
[KENSUKE chuckles]

352
00:19:44,708 --> 00:19:46,833
Just kidding!

353
00:19:46,916 --> 00:19:50,333
But save your tantrum until
we're out of here, okay?

354
00:19:50,416 --> 00:19:51,708
Now, then.

355
00:19:51,791 --> 00:19:54,625
Since you're here,
wanna help a bit more?

356
00:19:57,458 --> 00:20:00,666
[KENSUKE]
Whoa! So freakin' cool!

357
00:20:00,750 --> 00:20:02,500
You really are invincible!

358
00:20:02,583 --> 00:20:06,500
[OPERATOR E pants]

359
00:20:06,583 --> 00:20:08,291
[OPERATOR E]
Damn brats!

360
00:20:08,375 --> 00:20:11,916
[KENSUKE] Hey! A little
appreciation wouldn't hurt ya!

361
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:16,958
Jerk. Seriously, some people
are just impossible to please.

362
00:20:19,958 --> 00:20:20,625
[KENSUKE]
Hey.

363
00:20:20,708 --> 00:20:22,083
[gasps]

364
00:20:22,166 --> 00:20:25,166
Join me. Become a member of
the Boy Detective's Club.

365
00:20:26,375 --> 00:20:29,416
[KENSUKE] Together, we could
protect the people of this city.

366
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,416
[YOSHIO gasps]

367
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:31,833
[KENSUKE]
And as a sign-on bonus,

368
00:20:31,916 --> 00:20:34,958
I promise I'll find a
way to grant your wish.

369
00:20:35,041 --> 00:20:38,458
No matter what it takes.
One day, I'll kill you.

370
00:20:44,500 --> 00:20:45,875
[KENSUKE gasps]

371
00:20:49,958 --> 00:20:51,125
[YOSHIO shouts]

372
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:54,458
[KENSUKE gasps] Oh wow,
you shriek like a girl.

373
00:20:58,875 --> 00:21:00,291
[KENSUKE]
Does it hurt?

374
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:04,750
[KENSUKE] That's just
proof that you're still alive.

375
00:21:07,666 --> 00:21:11,166
[KENSUKE laughs]

376
00:21:11,250 --> 00:21:13,416
[KENSUKE]
Man, you really crack me up!

377
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:17,291
[laughing continues]

378
00:21:17,375 --> 00:21:21,333
[KENSUKE]
Oh yeah. I never got your name.

379
00:21:21,416 --> 00:21:24,583
Yoshio... Kobayashi.

380
00:21:24,666 --> 00:21:29,500
I see. So, Kobayashi,
wanna be my partner in fight--

381
00:21:29,583 --> 00:21:30,541
[KENSUKE grunts]

382
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:35,791
Hanasaki!

383
00:21:35,875 --> 00:21:37,125
[YOSHIO gasps]

384
00:21:39,291 --> 00:21:40,958
Get away from him, now!

385
00:21:41,041 --> 00:21:44,541
Put the gun down, Inoue.
It's not what it looks like.

386
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:47,500
Damn. Idiot!

387
00:21:49,041 --> 00:21:49,916
[gasps]

388
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,125
[whimpers]

389
00:21:51,208 --> 00:21:54,041
No. Make it stop!

390
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:58,208
[grunts]

391
00:22:01,291 --> 00:22:04,541
[gasps]

392
00:22:06,291 --> 00:22:11,041
[yells]

393
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,208
[AKECHI]
Um...

394
00:22:16,291 --> 00:22:18,250
Nao, dear?

395
00:22:18,333 --> 00:22:20,875
[NAO] Give it a rest.
That's all you're getting.

396
00:22:20,958 --> 00:22:23,875
You want more, do something
I can take credit for.

397
00:22:23,958 --> 00:22:27,333
[AKECHI] Man, future police
commissioners are scary.

398
00:22:27,416 --> 00:22:30,708
[NAO] So, any idea what
Twenty-Faces is after this time?

399
00:22:30,791 --> 00:22:33,208
[AKECHI] There'll be a separate
fee for that investigation.

400
00:22:33,291 --> 00:22:34,208
[groans]

401
00:22:34,291 --> 00:22:36,250
Okay. Refund me
for the first one.

402
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:38,250
I was just joshin' ya!

403
00:22:38,333 --> 00:22:41,208
Come on, Nao... Smile!

404
00:22:41,291 --> 00:22:44,791
Eh? Eh...?

405
00:22:44,875 --> 00:22:46,583
[20
"Hinomoto Heavy Industries

406
00:22:46,666 --> 00:22:50,625
ordered to suspend
operations indefinitely."

407
00:22:50,708 --> 00:22:52,250
[20 chuckles]

408
00:22:58,208 --> 00:23:02,250
Things are really going
to get fun now, Akechi.

409
00:23:12,125 --> 00:23:14,833
[YOSHIO exhales]

410
00:23:14,916 --> 00:23:16,875
[YOSHIO]
It tingles.

411
00:23:39,125 --> 00:23:41,291
[TWENTY-FACES]
"The Golden Traker."

